To fix the bug in the given function, we need to handle the case where the input string is `null`. Calling `toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH)` on a `null` string will result in a `NullPointerException`. We should first check if the input string is `null` and return an empty string in that case. Here is the corrected function:

```java
public static String lowerCase(final String input) {
    if (input == null) {
        return "";
    }
    return input.toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);
}
```
